{"sequence":24,"timestamp":"2026-04-24T21:13:52.656355937Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-505cdc61","body":"`resolve_bead_plan` still breaks valid membership checks when the live bead ID and the stored plan ID use different milestone aliases. In [src/cli/project.rs:1914-1918](/home/user/ralph-burning/src/cli/project.rs:1914) and [src/cli/project.rs:2013-2025](/home/user/ralph-burning/src/cli/project.rs:2013), any entry with `bead_id` goes through raw string comparison only, and the `Some(_)` branch no longer reaches the title-fallback path. A live bead returned as `bead-2` / `8.5.3` will therefore fail against a plan entry stored as `ms-alpha.bead-2` / `9ni.8.5.3`, even though the codebase already treats those forms as equivalent elsewhere ([src/contexts/milestone_record/bead_refs.rs:3-17](/home/user/ralph-burning/src/contexts/milestone_record/bead_refs.rs:3), [src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:3654-3670](/home/user/ralph-burning/src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:3654)). `project create-from-bead` can now reject a valid milestone/bead pair solely because `br show` returned the short form. Normalize both sides or reuse `milestone_bead_refs_match`, and add a regression test for short live IDs against qualified plan IDs.","dedup_key":"621ec430e8521b910500a1ac4e07ecf7aaa740da7d438a6d9824ede202bd922a","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260424200824","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":25,"timestamp":"2026-04-24T21:13:52.676837944Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-5709abda","body":"The legacy-plan warning is only deduplicated per process, not per milestone across CLI invocations. [src/cli/project.rs:1880-1893](/home/user/ralph-burning/src/cli/project.rs:1880) stores warned milestones in a process-local `OnceLock<Mutex<BTreeSet<String>>>`, and [src/cli/project.rs:1967-1980](/home/user/ralph-burning/src/cli/project.rs:1967) calls it from `project create-from-bead`. Because each CLI invocation starts a fresh process, operators will see the same warning every time they run the command for the same legacy milestone. The bead explicitly requires a one-time warning per milestone, not per invocation, so this needs a persisted marker or another cross-invocation mechanism.","dedup_key":"c772b9af84857c9f704968b8e8172eddd889b62d7f7749ff3aff8cacd3cff46f","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260424200824","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
