{"sequence":73,"timestamp":"2026-04-24T23:38:06.481003495Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-91373a14","body":"finding_summary: `resolve_bead_plan` now marks every legacy title-only match as `membership_confirmed = false`, and `execute_create_from_bead_in_dir` uses that flag to skip `validate_milestone_plan_snapshot` and to drop `plan_hash`/`plan_version` from the created project. That means a supported pre-change plan with no `bead_id` can silently bypass stale `status.json` detection and lose plan lineage metadata even when the title fallback resolved a unique bead successfully.\naffected_files:\n- src/cli/project.rs:373-392\n- src/cli/project.rs:2055-2072\nremediation_hint: keep the legacy warning path, but decouple it from snapshot/lineage validation. A unique successful legacy fallback should still validate the current plan snapshot and persist `plan_hash`/`plan_version`, or the code should introduce a separate flag for \"used legacy fallback\" instead of reusing `membership_confirmed` to disable those checks.","dedup_key":"15212b577f22657d0c056020d3428a68b86c1c817763eaa143c06c37ab1eb980","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260424200824","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
