{"sequence":97,"timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:48:26.210002139Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-7c7a6204","body":"finding_summary: Short dotted alias resolution can select a bead from the wrong milestone. `milestone_bead_refs_match` treats `8.5.3` as equivalent to `9ni.8.5.3` / `10.8.5.3` (`src/contexts/milestone_record/bead_refs.rs:3-49`), and `load_bead_detail`, `ensure_bead_belongs_to_milestone`, and `proposal_matches_bead_id` all trust that comparison (`src/cli/project.rs:1665-1755`, `src/cli/project.rs:1928-1937`, `src/cli/project.rs:2105-2113`). Another milestone with numeric id `8` can legitimately own bead `8.5.3`, so `project create-from-bead --milestone-id 10 --bead-id 8.5.3` can bind/claim the foreign bead instead of the planned `10.8.5.3`. remediation_hint: Do not treat arbitrary dotted ids as local aliases. Only accept a short dotted alias after resolving a bead that is proven to belong to the requested milestone (for example via the canonical `{milestone}.{alias}` form), and when the short-form lookup returns a foreign bead, continue to the canonical candidate instead of accepting or hard-failing immediately.","dedup_key":"bed78155ff4a3d8f08539b5821e7e2670c243d2be77d94ac02b0642592c2e73a","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260424200824","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
